===Adjective===
{{head|mul|adjective}}
# {{lb|mul|biology}} Having a [[male]] configuration of [[chromosome]]s as per the [[XY system]].
#* {{quote-text|en|termlang=mul|year=1973|author=E.W. Caspari|title=Advances in Genetics|page=334|isbn=0120176173|passage=For example. copulation of females with sterile males carrying deficient Y chromosomes lay as many eggs as do females inseminated by normal '''XY''' males.}}
#* '''1994''', R. V. Short, E. Balaban (eds), ''The Differences between the Sexes'', page 15, {{ISBN|052144411X}}.
#*: There is evidence to show that, occasionally, '''XY''' germ cells can undergo oogenesis when in an ovarian environment.
#* {{quote-text|en|termlang=mul|year=2009|author=Gerald N. Callahan|title=Between XX and XY: Intersexuality and the Myth of Two Sexes|page=30|isbn=1556527853|passage=The group at John Hopkins{{sic}}, as well as many others, dropped the "true sex" policy (such as XX or '''XY''') and adopted the "optimal gender" policy for assigning sex to sexually ambiguous children.}}
